Components:
Arduino Uno
Touch Sensor (e.g., TTP223)
LED
220 ohm resistor (for the LED)
Jumper wires
Breadboard (optional)

Connections:


Touch Sensor (TTP223) to Arduino:
VCC (Touch Sensor) → 5V (Arduino)
GND (Touch Sensor) → GND (Arduino)
SIG (Touch Sensor) → Pin 2 (Arduino)



LED to Arduino:
Anode (longer leg) of the LED → Pin 13 (Arduino)
Cathode (shorter leg) of the LED → One side of the 220-ohm resistor
The other side of the 220-ohm resistor → GND (Arduino)
